	(text "This is the Platter Detection System for the Zoetrope Carousel V4.\n\nThe system uses two photo-sensitive sensors (RPR-220) and a comparator to determine if a platter is loaded\non the machine or not.\n\nOne sensor lives on this PCB, the other on a separate PCB that connects to this PCB via connector J2. The\ntwo sensors must be mounted away from eachother. This sensor and PCB must be mounted beneith the platter\nloading aread on the machine, close enough to the center that it will be completely covered by the platter\nwhen a platter is loaded. The second sensor must be mounted away from the platter area in a position that \nwill never be bocked by the platter and not be blocked durring normal operation. Both sensors should be \ntuned to similar values and sensitivity. The sensor on this PCB, should have a large difference between no\nplatter and platter, the second sensor should be tuned for stable, no-sensor detection in comparison to \nthe sensor on this PCB (when no sensor is present).\n\nThe comparator on this PCB compares the two sensor values and if a sufficient difference is detected, it \ntoggles its output indicating if a platter is present or not. A potentiometer, R1, is used to tune the system.\n\nThe PCBs for the system are designed to be CNC milled at home using parts I already have."
		(exclude_from_sim no)
		(at 17.272 170.688 0)
		(effects
			(font
				(size 1.778 1.778)
			)
			(justify left)
		)
		(uuid "fb6fa118-c25c-4d9b-8d9f-f17857d0ff2b")
	)
